    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">803.01/10–449: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Heath</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-04">October 4,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received October 4—12:57 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>833. <hi rend="italic">Otechestven Front</hi> today publishes text of telegram to
                    Chou En-lai, Minister Foreign Affairs Central People’s Government Chinese
                    People’s Republic, acknowledging receipt of communication of October 1 from
                    latter government and stating Bulgarian Government will establish diplomatic
                    relations with People’s Republic China and exchange representatives.</p>
                <p>Also publishes article reporting establishment diplomatic relations between USSR
                    and People’s Republic China and breaking relations with Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Heath</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
